Disparaging someone for their dialect is crude. There is no "right" pronunciation, no one lexicon, and certainly no "proper" way to speak.
So yes, "aks" is a pronunciation of "ask," "warsh" is fine, "nukular" is a-ok, and "hyuge" and "yuge" are both great.
People speak differently based on where they live (geolect), their social class (sociolect), and their ethnicity (ethnolect).
There are 149 standard dialects of English across the world. 33 of them are dialects of American English.
Fun fact: if other people can understand what someone is saying, they're not "talking wrong." Language is not stagnant. It changes.
